</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugrizlor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grizlor</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/17/02 7:57:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1027.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://grizlorspics.iwarp.com/logo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RE: need help leading a naggy raid!</span><hr size=1> I've lead the last 3 sucessful naggy raids on my server myself with my monk. Nothing beats earning a reputation as a sucessful raid leader, especially if you are knowledgable, efficient and fair.<br>
<br>
First raid I lead... 5 groups, simply to test my toes. 3 or so deaths, didn't have the hang of it yet.<br>
<br>
Second Raid I did with 4 groups. Flawless kill.<br>
<br>
Last raid was with 3 groups, only 2 dedicated healers (1 cleric 1 druid). Paladins were doing backup heals, and it worked nicely. 2 deaths (The main Tank and the rogue).  You definitely want high damage output if you're going with less people... We didn't have any nukers, just monks, rogues, paladins (tanks who can spot heal are especially nice to keep their group healthy.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Couple pointers.<br>
<br>
As a warrior, you probably know that your taunt skill is innefective versus mobs of a higher level than you, unless you are level 55 or over. This applies to lord nagafen. Thus, the only thing you have to taunt him, is damage, and procs.  I've found that the best class for tanking lord Nagafen by FAR is a shadowknight. Buff him up with symbol and whatnot, give him a rune, and toss him a celestial healing right before he goes in.<br>
<br>
The shadowknight gets a 5-6 second head start, then have everyone else charge.  The SK runs in, agros naggy, And unloads his HT. Boom, instant high hate off the bat. Then he proceeds to lead naggy back to the rear of his lair. This is IMPORTANT. fighting on the bridge is bad.  Try to wall box him, have the SK fight with his back to the wall, and everyone else hitting at naggy's back from Max Melee range.<br>
<br>
Have all your other healers try to keep the SK going with spam heals... wait a bit more then you can begin CHs... I know a lot of raids fail because they try CHs and the clerics get agro and die. You simply have to be patient <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
Lastly, levels are your friend. Moreso than resist gear, levels significantly increase your rate of resisting the AEs. so capping the level at which people can come along is good. I would say 48+ if you are trying with less than 28 people.<br>
<br>
